# Next.js Data Fetching Constraints

Use React Server Components (RSC) as the direct data access layer.

- ALWAYS fetch data directly within Server Components.
- NEVER create intermediate Next.js App Router API routes (such as `app/api/...`) for internal UI data fetching.
- ONLY create Route Handlers (`route.ts`) when exposing endpoints to external third-party services, webhooks, or external clients.
- Await data fetching functions directly in async Server Components, and pass resolved data to Client Components only when interactivity is required.
